Class CampRegistrationValidation

java.lang.Object
CampRegistrationValidation
public class CampRegistrationValidation extends Object
The CampRegistrationValidation class provides methods for validating various conditions related to camp registration, such as checking whether a student is eligible to register for a camp, verifying registration status, detecting date clashes, and evaluating slot availability.

The class interacts with the Camp, Student, and CampList classes to perform validations. It utilizes an instance of ObjectFinder to locate student roles within a camp and to search for committee members across all camps.

The validations cover aspects such as open status, existing registrations, date clashes with other camps, registration deadlines, and slot availability for both attendees and committee members.
